2 DATE 18 DEC 1799
2 PLAC Mount Vernon, Fairfax, Virginia
1 NOTE First President of the United States (1789-1797) and Commander-in-Chief
2 CONT of the Continental Army during the American Revolution. Known as the
2 CONT "Father of His Country," he presided over the Constitutional Convention
2 CONT and set many precedents for the new nation's government. He married
2 CONT Martha Dandridge Custis in 1759. He had no biological children but
2 CONT raised Martha's children and grandchildren at Mount Vernon.
